&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;WORCESTERSHIRE ROYAL HOSPITAL&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;MEDICAL DAY CASE UNIT&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;STAFF NURSE - BAND 5&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for a motivated nurse, forward thinking and compassionate nurse to work within our nursing team to deliver our quality care agenda to the highest standard.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Medical Day Case carries out various evasive procedures and a variety of infusional therapies. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Therefore experience in venepuncture and cannulation, also the care of patients in a busy and challenging environment is essential.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;You must be a Registered General Nurse; experience in medical nursing is an advantage. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post would be suitable for qualified and newly qualified nurse.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will pride yourself on delivering high standards of nursing care, be flexible and have the ability to work in a busy environment caring for patients within the Medical Day Case Unit.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We require enthusiastic individuals who can work flexibly within the team over 6 day periods.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Hours of work are from 8.00 am to 9.00 pm to include Saturday over a 6 day period.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;In return you will receive development and training, also the support of a committed team of general and specialist nurses.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you feel you have the necessary skills and wish to be part of a friendly professional team we would be glad to receive your application, informal visits are welcomed.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For an informal visit or more information please contact:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Cathy Yapp, Unit Manager on Extn. 30597 via the hospital switchboard on 01905 763333 or Patience Ngundu, Matron on Bleep Number 753 via switchboard.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
